00:39:36,107 --> 00:39:37,842
Chef Sung-jun tastes the pasta.

969
00:39:37,908 --> 00:39:41,379
He said American pasta is
richer and greasier than Italian pasta.

970
00:39:41,445 --> 00:39:42,646
-Yes.
-I love it.

971
00:39:42,713 --> 00:39:45,282
Chef Hyun-suk's steak is out of the pan.

972
00:39:45,883 --> 00:39:48,052
-On top of that… What's that?
-What's that?

973
00:39:48,119 --> 00:39:51,355
The mix of cheese
and lion's mane mushrooms.

974
00:39:51,422 --> 00:39:53,891
-Oh, my. It looks good.
-Oh, my.

975
00:39:53,958 --> 00:39:55,893
WHY IS HE BRUSHING IT OFF AGAIN?

976
00:39:55,960 --> 00:39:58,929
-Why did you put it back?
-You topped it already.

977
00:39:58,996 --> 00:40:00,331
He's trying to make it look pretty.

978
00:40:00,398 --> 00:40:02,099
Because of presentation.

979
00:40:02,867 --> 00:40:04,502
He's trying to present it right.

980
00:40:04,568 --> 00:40:06,337
The steak is cooked perfectly.

981
00:40:06,404 --> 00:40:08,139
-Look at that.
-The steak looks perfect.

982
00:40:08,205 --> 00:40:10,908
-That's how she likes it.
-That's exactly how I love it.

983
00:40:10,975 --> 00:40:12,009
That's how you love it?

984
00:40:12,076 --> 00:40:16,080
Won-young wanted a dish
she'd see in fine dining restaurants.

985
00:40:16,680 --> 00:40:19,550
She said it had to look pretty too.

986
00:40:20,785 --> 00:40:23,921
-Sung-ju, can you go out to the field?
-Yes?

987
00:40:23,988 --> 00:40:25,156
We have five minutes left!

988
00:40:25,222 --> 00:40:26,390
Let me run out to the field.

989
00:40:26,457 --> 00:40:28,592
They both look so delicious!

990
00:40:28,659 --> 00:40:31,495
This is what I'm curious about.

991
00:40:31,562 --> 00:40:33,931
-It smells crazy.
-The pasta sauce.

992
00:40:33,998 --> 00:40:35,966
-It looks good.
-Sung-ju!

993
00:40:36,033 --> 00:40:38,869
-You should taste that.
-This one? The pasta sauce?

994
00:40:38,936 --> 00:40:40,704
It'll be totally my type.

995
00:40:40,771 --> 00:40:42,273
-I wonder how it'll taste.
-Yes.

996
00:40:42,339 --> 00:40:43,407
Let me have a taste.

997
00:40:43,474 --> 00:40:45,009
It has to be good.

998
00:40:45,075 --> 00:40:46,076
A TASTE OF THE SAUCE

999
00:40:46,143 --> 00:40:51,148
Will the sauce capture
the palate of lucky Vicky?

1000
00:40:53,284 --> 00:40:54,385
Is it rich and creamy?

1001
00:40:54,452 --> 00:40:55,886
It's really creamy.

1002
00:40:56,620 --> 00:40:57,855
-How is it?
-It's really creamy.

1003
00:40:57,922 --> 00:41:00,357
I love it.

1004
00:41:00,424 --> 00:41:03,661
She says she loves it.
She loves the creamy taste.

1005
00:41:03,727 --> 00:41:05,696
Does it have to be this rich?

1006
00:41:05,763 --> 00:41:08,098
Do you need it to be this rich and creamy?

1007
00:41:08,165 --> 00:41:09,834
Is it deliciously creamy or just creamy?

1008
00:41:09,900 --> 00:41:11,402
It's a little bland.

1009
00:41:11,469 --> 00:41:14,538
-It's bland?
-It just tasted creamy, and that's all.

1010
00:41:14,605 --> 00:41:16,040
There's no savory taste.

1011
00:41:16,106 --> 00:41:17,141
Please add some salt.

1012
00:41:17,208 --> 00:41:18,209
He's telling you to try that.

1013
00:41:18,275 --> 00:41:19,543
He wants you to try his food.

1014
00:41:19,610 --> 00:41:20,845
He wants you to try that.

1015
00:41:22,213 --> 00:41:23,214
THIS AND THIS

1016
00:41:23,280 --> 00:41:25,382
-He wants you to try two things.
-I will.

1017
00:41:25,449 --> 00:41:27,384
This is the topping.

1018
00:41:27,451 --> 00:41:29,920
-It's really thick.
-Thick.

1019
00:41:29,987 --> 00:41:31,455
-It looks thick.
-It's thick.

1020
00:41:32,156 --> 00:41:34,291
-Rich, creamy Vicky.
-Is it rich and creamy Vicky?

1021
00:41:34,358 --> 00:41:35,793
-How is it?
-How is it?

1022
00:41:36,393 --> 00:41:38,429
This tastes like

1023
00:41:38,496 --> 00:41:40,831
Gorgonzola pizza.

1024
00:41:40,898 --> 00:41:42,500
It totally tastes like that.

1025
00:41:42,566 --> 00:41:45,369
TOTALLY RICH AND CREAMY

1026
00:41:45,436 --> 00:41:47,271
That sounds so good.

1027
00:41:48,072 --> 00:41:49,373
You have three minutes.

1028
00:41:51,575 --> 00:41:53,611
JUMPY

1029
00:41:55,613 --> 00:41:59,450
ADDING SOY HOT POT SAUCE
TO THE BLAND SAUCE

1030
00:41:59,517 --> 00:42:02,186
CHOI HYUN-SUK PULLS OUT A TORCH

1031
00:42:02,753 --> 00:42:05,155
CHEESE STEAK ON FIRE

1032
00:42:06,690 --> 00:42:08,492
-The torch.
-The torch.

1033
00:42:08,559 --> 00:42:09,660
What's he doing?

1034
00:42:09,727 --> 00:42:10,761
I'm melting the cheese.

1035
00:42:11,762 --> 00:42:13,163
Is the meat inside?

1036
00:42:13,230 --> 00:42:14,665
-The steak.
-The steak is there.

1037
00:42:15,933 --> 00:42:18,736
THE CHEESE IS DEFINITELY MELTING

1038
00:42:18,802 --> 00:42:20,638
Do you have any leftover steak?

1039
00:42:20,704 --> 00:42:22,640
SWAMPED

1040
00:42:22,706 --> 00:42:23,707
What are you doing?

1041
00:42:24,742 --> 00:42:27,111
GOAL

1042
00:42:27,177 --> 00:42:28,312
-Sung-ju!
-Yes?

1043
00:42:28,379 --> 00:42:29,947
You have to eat it,
even if you're embarrassed.

1044
00:42:30,014 --> 00:42:32,449
You have to taste it!

1045
00:42:32,516 --> 00:42:35,352
-Taste it and see if it's evenly grilled.
-My gosh.

1046
00:42:35,920 --> 00:42:37,021
-That's our job!
-Yes.

1047
00:42:37,087 --> 00:42:38,489
-Let me taste this.
-Okay.

1048
00:42:38,556 --> 00:42:40,558
Let's see if it was cooked evenly.

1049
00:42:40,624 --> 00:42:43,127
-It looks so good.
-Let me taste it.

1050
00:42:44,628 --> 00:42:46,597
-Was it cooked evenly?
-The steak looks great.

1051
00:42:46,664 --> 00:42:48,599
-Was it cooked evenly?
-The steak looks great.

1052
00:42:49,600 --> 00:42:53,203
-It looks good.
-But the problem is, it's a little salty.

1053
00:42:53,270 --> 00:42:55,205
He sprinkled salt
one more time in the end.

1054
00:42:55,272 --> 00:42:57,007
WILL HIS LAST SHOW CAUSE HIS LOSS?

1055
00:42:57,074 --> 00:42:59,209
The meat and the salt don't really match.

1056
00:42:59,276 --> 00:43:00,678
No.

1057
00:43:00,744 --> 00:43:02,212
You just had the edge.

1058
00:43:03,414 --> 00:43:05,082
-Is that why?
-That's the edge.

1059
00:43:05,816 --> 00:43:09,420
I see. You weren't using the edges.

1060
00:43:09,486 --> 00:43:12,056
The edges must be salty,
but not the insides.

1061
00:43:12,122 --> 00:43:13,657
So it's supposed to be salty?

1062
00:43:13,724 --> 00:43:16,627
I see. He's plating the dish.

1063
00:43:16,694 --> 00:43:19,129
-The carrots go in the middle.
-Carrots.

1064
00:43:19,196 --> 00:43:21,398
-You have a minute and 30 seconds.
-A minute and 30 seconds.

1065
00:43:22,800 --> 00:43:24,401
Why does time fly by?

1066
00:43:24,468 --> 00:43:25,736
Right?

1067
00:43:25,803 --> 00:43:27,471
-Arugula.
-Arugula.

1068
00:43:27,538 --> 00:43:29,440
5. ADD ARUGULA TO DRESSING AND MIX

1069
00:43:30,007 --> 00:43:31,942
HE SERVES THE SALAD RIGHT AWAY

1070
00:43:32,576 --> 00:43:34,244
His dish isn't ready yet.

1071
00:43:34,311 --> 00:43:36,747
-The pasta isn't out yet.
-He needs to make pasta and salad!

1072
00:43:36,814 --> 00:43:38,349
The pasta isn't out yet.

1073
00:43:38,415 --> 00:43:39,883
-No, it is.
-Is the pasta ready?

1074
00:43:39,950 --> 00:43:42,886
I hope the brisket doesn't get tough.

1075
00:43:42,953 --> 00:43:45,055
6. TOP ARUGULA
WITH STRAWBERRY AND GOAT CHEESE

1076
00:43:45,122 --> 00:43:47,625
I hope the brisket doesn't get tough.

1077
00:43:47,691 --> 00:43:49,193
-Was it seasoned well?
-The brisket.

1078
00:43:49,259 --> 00:43:53,063
Let me taste the brisket.

1079
00:43:53,130 --> 00:43:54,298
-Sung-ju!
-Yes?

1080
00:43:54,365 --> 00:43:56,934
It'll be tough to eat
when it's overcooked.

1081
00:43:57,001 --> 00:43:58,002
Is it tender?

1082
00:43:58,068 --> 00:44:01,872
HOW WAS THE BRISKET COOKED?

1083
00:44:01,939 --> 00:44:04,208
-Is it tender? It's tough!
-It's tough!

1084
00:44:04,274 --> 00:44:07,478
-Kwon Sung-jun! It's tough! Kwon Sung-jun!
-It's tough!

1085
00:44:07,544 --> 00:44:09,380
Brisket shouldn't be tough.

1086
00:44:09,947 --> 00:44:11,248
THE NEW SHOW-OFF CHEF
IS IN A CRISIS

1087
00:44:11,315 --> 00:44:12,616
Brisket shouldn't be tough.

1088
00:44:12,683 --> 00:44:13,884
It's a little tough.

1089
00:44:13,951 --> 00:44:15,352
THE ORIGINAL SHOW-OFF CHEF
SPEEDS UP

1090
00:44:15,419 --> 00:44:16,420
Hurry up.

1091
00:44:16,987 --> 00:44:18,989
11. TOP WITH CHOPPED ARUGULA

1092
00:44:19,056 --> 00:44:21,725
AND THE SAUCE USED
TO BOIL DOWN CARROTS

1093
00:44:24,495 --> 00:44:26,130
CHOI HYUN-SUK
FINISHES LUCKY CHOI STEAK

1094
00:44:26,196 --> 00:44:28,666
HE FINISHES IT
50 SECONDS BEFORE THE TIME

1095
00:44:28,732 --> 00:44:30,134
Choi Hyun-suk is done.

1096
00:44:30,200 --> 00:44:33,337
-You need to work with this brisket.
-Slowly.

1097
00:44:33,404 --> 00:44:35,339
-Slowly.
-It's under a minute.

1098
00:44:35,406 --> 00:44:37,474
-You can do it, Chef Sung-jun!
-It's all fine.

1099
00:44:37,541 --> 00:44:38,676
Into the pasta.

1100
00:44:38,742 --> 00:44:40,811
Is he cooking brisket once again?

1101
00:44:40,878 --> 00:44:43,847
I don't know how it'll be.

1102
00:44:43,914 --> 00:44:47,718
-It was a bit tough for my taste.
-You have 30 seconds left!

1103
00:44:48,352 --> 00:44:50,354
You have 30 seconds left! My gosh.

1104
00:44:51,855 --> 00:44:54,658
You have 25 seconds left, Sung-jun.

1105
00:44:54,725 --> 00:44:58,262
-Choi Hyun-suk is already done.
-Twenty-five seconds.

1106
00:44:58,328 --> 00:45:00,330
This is so nerve-racking.

1107
00:45:00,397 --> 00:45:02,933
The brisket is now inside the pasta.

1108
00:45:03,000 --> 00:45:04,802
I'm so nervous!

1109
00:45:04,868 --> 00:45:07,204
Chef Sung-jun, you can do it.
Don't be nervous.

1110
00:45:07,971 --> 00:45:08,972
What?

1111
00:45:11,408 --> 00:45:12,409
-Ten!
-Ten!

1112
00:45:12,476 --> 00:45:14,311
-Nine! Eight!
-Nine! Eight!

1113
00:45:14,378 --> 00:45:15,679
Hurry up.

1114
00:45:15,746 --> 00:45:17,715
-Seven! Six!
-Seven! Six!

1115
00:45:17,781 --> 00:45:19,750
-Five! Four!
-Five! Four!

1116
00:45:19,817 --> 00:45:21,018
-Three!
-Three!

1117
00:45:21,085 --> 00:45:22,186
-Two!
-Two!

1118
00:45:22,252 --> 00:45:23,787
-One! He's done.
-One!

1119
00:45:23,854 --> 00:45:27,458
Chef Sung-jun finished everything.

1120
00:45:27,524 --> 00:45:30,194
That was so amazing.

1121
00:45:30,260 --> 00:45:33,731
-It smells so good!
-It smells so wonderful.

1122
00:45:34,665 --> 00:45:36,066
My goodness.

1123
00:45:37,468 --> 00:45:39,536
These look amazing.

1124
00:45:39,603 --> 00:45:40,604
They look so pretty.

1125
00:45:40,671 --> 00:45:42,005
I can't believe it.

1126
00:45:44,808 --> 00:45:49,012
THE SPIRIT
OF AUTHENTIC ITALIAN CUISINE!

1127
00:45:50,414 --> 00:45:54,918
CAMEMBERT, GOAT CHEESE, CHEDDAR,
AND MOZZARELLA COVERING THE STEAK

1128
00:45:55,619 --> 00:45:59,456
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S
LUCKY CHOI STEAK

1129
00:45:59,523 --> 00:46:00,557
It's so pretty.

1130
00:46:00,624 --> 00:46:03,761
First, it's really pretty,
and it's in a style that I love.

1131
00:46:03,827 --> 00:46:06,130
WON-YOUNG ALREADY LOVES
THE PRESENTATION

1132
00:46:06,196 --> 00:46:07,831
I love these details too.

1133
00:46:07,898 --> 00:46:10,667
He could've just grilled the carrots
and put it here,

1134
00:46:10,734 --> 00:46:13,036
but even in that short while,
he thought of presentation

1135
00:46:13,103 --> 00:46:16,039
-and put holes in them.
-He did.

1136
00:46:16,106 --> 00:46:18,809
These look amazing, and I like it.

1137
00:46:19,409 --> 00:46:21,512
I didn't want to miss

1138
00:46:21,578 --> 00:46:22,713
anything you mentioned.

1139
00:46:25,382 --> 00:46:27,151
You're something.

1140
00:46:27,718 --> 00:46:29,019
-You are.
-He's good.

1141
00:46:29,086 --> 00:46:30,387
Try the steak first,

1142
00:46:30,454 --> 00:46:33,023
then have some garnish if it's too rich.

1143
00:46:33,090 --> 00:46:34,691
-Look at the cheese.
-My gosh.

1144
00:46:34,758 --> 00:46:38,195
The cheese topping already looks so good.

1145
00:46:38,262 --> 00:46:40,364
You can take turns
to eat the steak and the garnish.

1146
00:46:40,430 --> 00:46:42,866
-You said the steak was too salty.
-It was.

1147
00:46:42,933 --> 00:46:45,602
She takes a bite.
She prefers steak in medium-rare.

1148
00:46:45,669 --> 00:46:46,870
MMM

1149
00:46:46,937 --> 00:46:48,005
Mmm!

1150
00:46:48,071 --> 00:46:49,673
-Mmm!
-That was quick.

1151
00:46:50,374 --> 00:46:52,676
SHE MAKES AN AMAZED SOUND
AFTER ONE BITE

1152
00:46:54,077 --> 00:46:56,146
EYES WIDENED

1153
00:46:56,713 --> 00:47:00,417
A happy sound came out of her mouth.

1154
00:47:00,484 --> 00:47:01,618
"Mmm!"

1155
00:47:01,685 --> 00:47:03,587
Ladies make dolphin sounds
when the food is good.

1156
00:47:03,654 --> 00:47:05,455
-You're right.
-"Mmm!"

1157
00:47:05,522 --> 00:47:08,425
-It's really good.
-Is it?

1158
00:47:08,492 --> 00:47:09,660
The steak was cooked

1159
00:47:09,726 --> 00:47:11,128
in the most even way possible.

1160
00:47:12,596 --> 00:47:14,097
Isn't it salty?

1161
00:47:14,164 --> 00:47:16,333
No, he cut out the edges

1162
00:47:16,400 --> 00:47:19,102
-and gave me the tastiest part.
-Yes.

1163
00:47:19,169 --> 00:47:21,638
The middle part is perfect.
It's not too salty.

1164
00:47:22,639 --> 00:47:24,741
-Let me try the carrot.
-The carrot.

1165
00:47:26,543 --> 00:47:27,845
Mmm.

1166
00:47:27,911 --> 00:47:29,880
It doesn't taste like carrot.

1167
00:47:29,947 --> 00:47:32,015
-It's like fruit preserves.
-I see.

1168
00:47:32,082 --> 00:47:35,953
-It tastes like sweet fruit salad.
-Fruit salad?

1169
00:47:36,019 --> 00:47:38,555
-The carrot tastes like fruit?
-Yes.

1170
00:47:38,622 --> 00:47:41,358
I was hoping you'd take a bigger portion.

1171
00:47:41,425 --> 00:47:42,860
Try and take a bigger bite.

1172
00:47:42,926 --> 00:47:44,661
I have a small mouth.

1173
00:47:44,728 --> 00:47:46,763
OH, NO

1174
00:47:46,830 --> 00:47:49,700
-Listen.
-How can she do that with a small mouth?

1175
00:47:49,766 --> 00:47:52,069
You asked someone with a small mouth
to take a big bite.

1176
00:47:52,135 --> 00:47:54,137
What you said was really accurate, though.

1177
00:47:54,204 --> 00:47:55,539
I take really small bites.

1178
00:47:55,606 --> 00:47:57,274
-I hoped you'd feel the richness.
-Right.

1179
00:47:57,341 --> 00:47:59,576
If you take a little bigger bite,

1180
00:47:59,643 --> 00:48:01,912
-it'll feel even richer.
-The richness.

1181
00:48:01,979 --> 00:48:05,215
-Try to take a bigger bite, Won-young.
-Yes, I see.

1182
00:48:05,282 --> 00:48:06,717
Rich and creamy Vicky.

1183
00:48:06,783 --> 00:48:08,118
CUTTING OUT A BIG PIECE

1184
00:48:08,185 --> 00:48:09,186
Look at the cheese.

1185
00:48:09,253 --> 00:48:10,354
It gets cut so easily.

1186
00:48:10,420 --> 00:48:13,190
Yes, it's very easy to cut.
It's not tough at all.

1187
00:48:15,025 --> 00:48:16,727
A BIG BITE

1188
00:48:18,362 --> 00:48:19,663
Oh.

1189
00:48:20,297 --> 00:48:21,465
It must feel different.

1190
00:48:21,531 --> 00:48:23,233
Oh.

1191
00:48:23,300 --> 00:48:24,468
It must feel different.

1192
00:48:24,534 --> 00:48:26,536
-It must be.
-I see.

1193
00:48:26,603 --> 00:48:28,205
-Is it different?
-How was the bigger bite?

1194
00:48:28,272 --> 00:48:30,974
I need to start practicing
taking bigger bites.

1195
00:48:31,041 --> 00:48:32,442
It tastes much better.

1196
00:48:33,277 --> 00:48:35,312
-I see.
-So it can be different.

1197
00:48:35,379 --> 00:48:38,548
How did you make this sauce?

1198
00:48:38,615 --> 00:48:41,618
Camembert cheese has a lighter taste,

1199
00:48:41,685 --> 00:48:45,389
so I mixed goat cheese and cheddar cheese

1200
00:48:45,455 --> 00:48:47,791
to make it richer and thicker

1201
00:48:47,858 --> 00:48:50,193
just the way you wanted it.

1202
00:48:50,260 --> 00:48:52,496
It was overly rich for my taste before.
Is it okay?

1203
00:48:52,562 --> 00:48:54,898
This is perfect, actually.

1204
00:48:54,965 --> 00:48:57,301
If it were less rich,

1205
00:48:57,367 --> 00:48:59,369
I wouldn't have made that dolphin sound.

1206
00:49:02,105 --> 00:49:06,076
CREAM PASTA MEETS PISTACHIO

1207
00:49:07,210 --> 00:49:09,913
MADE JUST FOR WON-YOUNG,
STRAWBERRY ARUGULA SALAD

1208
00:49:11,381 --> 00:49:14,051
CHEF KWON SUNG-JUN'S
PISTACHIO ACCENDIO

1209
00:49:14,117 --> 00:49:15,953
-The salad.
-The salad first.

1210
00:49:16,019 --> 00:49:17,788
-The salad first.
-She goes for the salad first.

1211
00:49:18,388 --> 00:49:20,557
HOW WILL IT TASTE?

1212
00:49:21,992 --> 00:49:23,493
She tastes everything together.

1213
00:49:24,695 --> 00:49:25,862
1 FROWN

1214
00:49:25,929 --> 00:49:27,664
She just frowned.

1215
00:49:27,731 --> 00:49:29,132
Does it taste different?

1216
00:49:29,199 --> 00:49:31,034
-We just got one dolphin.
-Yes.

1217
00:49:31,601 --> 00:49:33,971
-Two, three.
-Three, no, four.

1218
00:49:34,037 --> 00:49:36,006
We have a dolphin family.

1219
00:49:36,073 --> 00:49:38,208
I only had goat cheese

1220
00:49:38,275 --> 00:49:40,610
with chestnut honey at home.

1221
00:49:40,677 --> 00:49:44,081
I need to start mixing
pistachio spread with chestnut honey.

1222
00:49:46,183 --> 00:49:49,286
This was the best salad I've ever had.

1223
00:49:49,353 --> 00:49:50,654
-The best salad of her life.
-The salad?

1224
00:49:50,721 --> 00:49:51,722
I really mean it.

1225
00:49:51,788 --> 00:49:55,692
-You were worried he used it up.
-He emptied it out.

1226
00:49:55,759 --> 00:49:57,027
Was it worth the amount?

1227
00:49:57,094 --> 00:49:58,595
It was totally worth the amount.

1228
00:49:59,596 --> 00:50:01,832
I decided to order one on my way home.

1229
00:50:01,898 --> 00:50:03,567
I see. Okay.

1230
00:50:03,633 --> 00:50:06,003
And now,

1231
00:50:06,069 --> 00:50:09,306
the battle is up to the pasta,
but the pasta is…

1232
00:50:09,373 --> 00:50:11,241
But the pasta is…

1233
00:50:11,308 --> 00:50:12,309
DID IT GET SOGGY?

1234
00:50:12,376 --> 00:50:14,311
But I totally understand.

1235
00:50:14,378 --> 00:50:18,048
Quite a while has passed, so the richness…

1236
00:50:18,115 --> 00:50:19,116
-Oh, no.
-Wait.

1237
00:50:19,182 --> 00:50:22,419
-Will it be all right? It was the time.
-But I…

1238
00:50:22,486 --> 00:50:25,288
But I took this time into consideration
when I cooked the pasta.

1239
00:50:25,856 --> 00:50:27,624
-Really?
-It'll taste perfect.

1240
00:50:27,691 --> 00:50:31,061
He took this time into consideration
and knew she'd eat it later.

1241
00:50:31,128 --> 00:50:32,596
You even thought of that?

1242
00:50:33,730 --> 00:50:34,731
So?

1243
00:50:34,798 --> 00:50:36,166
EVERYONE IS IN DISBELIEF

1244
00:50:40,437 --> 00:50:42,639
WHAT WILL SHE SAY ABOUT THE PASTA?

1245
00:50:45,742 --> 00:50:46,743
Mmm!

1246
00:50:47,978 --> 00:50:49,946
I keep making the dolphin sound.

1247
00:50:50,647 --> 00:50:51,915
PHEW

1248
00:50:51,982 --> 00:50:53,517
It must be good.

1249
00:50:54,284 --> 00:50:55,952
It did not get soggy at all.

1250
00:50:56,019 --> 00:50:57,487
It didn't?

1251
00:50:57,554 --> 00:50:59,322
The cream got thicker,

1252
00:50:59,389 --> 00:51:01,658
but the pasta isn't soggy at all.
You'll see when you try it.

1253
00:51:01,725 --> 00:51:03,326
THE HUMAN PASTA TIMER

1254
00:51:03,393 --> 00:51:04,694
He thought of that?

1255
00:51:04,761 --> 00:51:06,763
I thought this was
another lucky Vicky moment.

1256
00:51:06,830 --> 00:51:10,700
This pasta became cheese itself
because some time had passed.

1257
00:51:10,767 --> 00:51:12,769
The pasta sauce
seeps into the noodles after a while.

1258
00:51:12,836 --> 00:51:14,104
Right. I get it.

1259
00:51:14,171 --> 00:51:15,172
It becomes thicker.

1260
00:51:15,238 --> 00:51:16,773
Next, let me try some meat.

1261
00:51:16,840 --> 00:51:20,377
-Yes, I was worried about the meat.
-Try it with the meat.

1262
00:51:20,444 --> 00:51:23,880
I thought he cooked the brisket
a little too early.

1263
00:51:25,415 --> 00:51:27,117
What?

1264
00:51:28,018 --> 00:51:29,186
It's tender.

1265
00:51:29,252 --> 00:51:30,253
-It is?
-Yes.

1266
00:51:30,320 --> 00:51:31,321
That's odd.

1267
00:51:31,388 --> 00:51:34,191
The meat mixed with this sauce
feels really tender.

1268
00:51:34,791 --> 00:51:36,526
That's a wonder.

1269
00:51:36,593 --> 00:51:37,594
-It's not tough at all.
-Really?

1270
00:51:37,661 --> 00:51:40,530
You tossed the meat
with the noodles one last time.

1271
00:51:40,597 --> 00:51:41,698
You're right.

1272
00:51:41,765 --> 00:51:45,402
The meat becomes tender
when it's mixed with sauce.

1273
00:51:45,469 --> 00:51:46,470
-I had that on my mind.
-It's science.

1274
00:51:46,536 --> 00:51:47,537
I only had the meat.

1275
00:51:47,604 --> 00:51:51,608
It kind of feels like
the battle is going to Sung-jun.

1276
00:51:51,675 --> 00:51:54,077
I enjoyed both dishes very much.

1277
00:51:54,144 --> 00:51:55,846
So? Were they both rich and creamy?

1278
00:51:55,912 --> 00:51:58,148
It was totally rich, creamy Vicky!

1279
00:52:01,885 --> 00:52:05,288
Not many people can make her do this.

1280
00:52:05,355 --> 00:52:07,190
-Let's try some too.
-Yes.

1281
00:52:07,257 --> 00:52:08,391
First, Chef Hyun-suk.

1282
00:52:08,458 --> 00:52:09,759
I'm really curious.

1283
00:52:09,826 --> 00:52:11,161
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S
LUCKY CHOI STEAK

1284
00:52:11,228 --> 00:52:13,763
Let's take a bite. This is…

1285
00:52:13,830 --> 00:52:14,831
1 FROWN

1286
00:52:14,898 --> 00:52:17,300
Try the carrot too.

1287
00:52:17,367 --> 00:52:19,069
It's not salty at all.

1288
00:52:19,136 --> 00:52:21,104
-It doesn't seem too rich or creamy.
-Right?

1289
00:52:21,171 --> 00:52:24,107
And steak tastes great with cheese.

1290
00:52:24,174 --> 00:52:27,677
It feels like grilled beef intestines,

1291
00:52:27,744 --> 00:52:30,147
as if the fat is already with the meat.

1292
00:52:30,213 --> 00:52:32,649
-It tasted like one ingredient.
-Yes.

1293
00:52:32,716 --> 00:52:34,417
How is it, Chef Kang-rok?

1294
00:52:34,484 --> 00:52:36,286
-It's good.
-Is it?

1295
00:52:36,353 --> 00:52:37,420
Yes, the steak.

1296
00:52:37,487 --> 00:52:39,356
The steak is delicious.

1297
00:52:39,422 --> 00:52:40,924
SHE'S ON A GOURMET TRIP ALL ALONE

1298
00:52:40,991 --> 00:52:42,459
A HEARTY BITE

1299
00:52:43,927 --> 00:52:45,629
I tried the part he cut off.

1300
00:52:45,695 --> 00:52:47,898
I see why he cut it off.

1301
00:52:47,964 --> 00:52:49,032
Yes, it goes so well.

1302
00:52:49,099 --> 00:52:50,100
CHUCKLING

1303
00:52:50,667 --> 00:52:51,968
SHE GOT CAUGHT

1304
00:52:52,035 --> 00:52:53,637
Won-young eats so well.

1305
00:52:54,204 --> 00:52:55,305
EMBARRASSED

1306
00:52:55,372 --> 00:52:56,840
She keeps eating.

1307
00:52:56,907 --> 00:52:58,575
THE TWO WHO MADE HER FORGET
THAT IT'S TV

1308
00:52:59,276 --> 00:53:01,778
-I didn't think she'd eat a lot.
-She has to make a choice soon.

1309
00:53:01,845 --> 00:53:04,447
-She has to decide.
-I actually didn't hear you.

1310
00:53:04,514 --> 00:53:06,082
You didn't hear us talk?

1311
00:53:06,149 --> 00:53:08,685
-This was so good.
-She was dining.

1312
00:53:08,752 --> 00:53:09,953
That's even better.

1313
00:53:10,020 --> 00:53:11,087
Yes, of course.

1314
00:53:11,154 --> 00:53:12,756
She has to make
an important decision soon.

1315
00:53:12,822 --> 00:53:14,891
Please feel free to keep dining.

1316
00:53:14,958 --> 00:53:16,459
This time,

1317
00:53:16,526 --> 00:53:20,497
-let's try Pistachio Accendio by Sung-jun.
-Yes.

1318
00:53:20,564 --> 00:53:23,033
-This is…
-Pistachio Accendio.

1319
00:53:23,099 --> 00:53:24,768
The meat was tough before.

1320
00:53:28,271 --> 00:53:29,272
EYES WIDENED

1321
00:53:29,339 --> 00:53:31,608
-It's not tough.
-It's not.

1322
00:53:31,675 --> 00:53:34,644
I was really worried before.

1323
00:53:34,711 --> 00:53:37,847
If it was just cream,
it'd be the taste we were used to.

1324
00:53:37,914 --> 00:53:40,617
But the bit of pistachio spread
he dropped in

1325
00:53:40,684 --> 00:53:43,486
-played a huge role for this dish.
-You're right.

1326
00:53:43,553 --> 00:53:46,289
It wasn't just rich and creamy,
but it had a mixture of flavor.

1327
00:53:46,356 --> 00:53:48,191
I was a little worried

1328
00:53:48,258 --> 00:53:50,827
because this was similar
to something I was thinking.

1329
00:53:50,894 --> 00:53:52,896
Is it similar to what you'll make?

1330
00:53:52,963 --> 00:53:55,298
It could be similar.

1331
00:53:55,365 --> 00:53:58,201
The experts have
a similar way of thinking.

1332
00:53:58,268 --> 00:54:01,071
Now, many things are at stake.

1333
00:54:01,137 --> 00:54:02,572
A star,

1334
00:54:02,639 --> 00:54:04,374
a nickname,

1335
00:54:04,441 --> 00:54:07,477
and someone's frying pan.

1336
00:54:07,544 --> 00:54:10,480
-Now, Chef Hyun-suk's dish is one.
-So?

1337
00:54:10,547 --> 00:54:13,049
Chef Sung-jun's dish is two.

1338
00:54:13,116 --> 00:54:15,051
-I pressed it.
-You did?

1339
00:54:15,118 --> 00:54:18,321
Who will become the winner?

1340
00:54:18,388 --> 00:54:22,225
Are we going to see
Little Choi Hyun-suk or Old Matfia?

1341
00:54:22,292 --> 00:54:25,228
Who did Won-young choose? Show us!

1342
00:54:25,295 --> 00:54:26,796
Oh, no.

1343
00:54:26,863 --> 00:54:28,398
"Oh, no."

1344
00:54:28,465 --> 00:54:33,870
Which dish did she think was
richer and creamier?

1345
00:54:33,937 --> 00:54:34,938
Gosh.

1346
00:54:35,005 --> 00:54:36,139
Who's the winner?

1347
00:54:36,206 --> 00:54:38,908
Which one is the winner?

1348
00:54:39,542 --> 00:54:42,312
Choi Hyun-suk versus Kwon Sung-jun!

1349
00:54:42,379 --> 00:54:45,515
-Who did Won-young choose?
-Who is it?

1350
00:54:45,582 --> 00:54:47,617
Who's the winner?

1351
00:54:47,684 --> 00:54:49,019
CHOI HYUN-SUK WINS

1352
00:54:49,486 --> 00:54:50,487
Who's the winner?

1353
00:54:50,553 --> 00:54:51,888
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S
LUCKY CHOI STEAK WINS

1354
00:54:51,955 --> 00:54:53,156
What a twist.

1355
00:54:53,657 --> 00:54:55,558
It was Choi Hyun-suk.

1356
00:54:56,192 --> 00:54:59,329
IT'S ME, CHOI HYUN-SUK

1357
00:55:01,364 --> 00:55:04,134
EVERYONE LAUGHS
AT HIS SHOW-OFF CELEBRATION

1358
00:55:05,101 --> 00:55:08,371
-Oh, no. My gosh.
-That was a huge twist.

1359
00:55:09,739 --> 00:55:12,609
We thought it'd be Sung-jun.

1360
00:55:12,676 --> 00:55:13,877
If I had to pick

1361
00:55:13,943 --> 00:55:16,946
just one of the two dishes,
it would've been Chef Matfia.

1362
00:55:17,013 --> 00:55:19,516
But when I went back to ground zero
and thought about it,

1363
00:55:19,582 --> 00:55:23,553
I had to consider
who used cheese more effectively.

1364
00:55:24,254 --> 00:55:27,924
I thought this dish
brought out cheese even more,

1365
00:55:27,991 --> 00:55:30,860
-so I chose Chef Hyun-suk.
-That was your judgment.

1366
00:55:30,927 --> 00:55:33,663
-That was how I dared to pick one.
-I see.

1367
00:55:33,730 --> 00:55:34,831
IT'S OKAY

1368
00:55:34,898 --> 00:55:36,933
-In this case…
-It must've been hard.

1369
00:55:37,000 --> 00:55:39,936
Chef Hyun-suk gets three stars.

1370
00:55:41,538 --> 00:55:44,007
His lips are about to come up to his eyes.

1371
00:55:44,574 --> 00:55:46,810
-The flounder smile.
-The flounder.

1372
00:55:46,876 --> 00:55:49,846
-The flounder smile.
-He shows the flounder smile.

1373
00:55:49,913 --> 00:55:52,582
Chef Hyun-suk, please share a word.

1374
00:55:52,649 --> 00:55:54,451
I don't have much to say.

1375
00:55:54,517 --> 00:55:56,853
If you do your best to cook a dish

1376
00:55:56,920 --> 00:55:58,788
just as your client asks,

1377
00:55:58,855 --> 00:56:00,523
then you'll automatically be lucky Vicky.

1378
00:56:02,392 --> 00:56:03,393
Congratulations.

1379
00:56:03,460 --> 00:56:06,162
He just said that
and began to read my countenance.

1380
00:56:06,229 --> 00:56:07,997
HE WAS AFRAID SHE'D ATTACK HIM AGAIN

1381
00:56:08,064 --> 00:56:09,065
In case you say something.

1382
00:56:10,200 --> 00:56:11,301
He looked at me like this.

1383
00:56:11,368 --> 00:56:14,704
Chef Sung-jun, now,

1384
00:56:14,771 --> 00:56:15,872
you'll be Little Hyun-suk.

1385
00:56:15,939 --> 00:56:17,707
-Napoli Matfia…
-Wait, Little Hyun-suk?

1386
00:56:18,541 --> 00:56:19,542
Why not?

1387
00:56:19,609 --> 00:56:22,078
He's a diligent cook and all,
so I want to protect him.

1388
00:56:22,145 --> 00:56:25,482
Let's call him Baby Hyun-suk.

1389
00:56:26,616 --> 00:56:28,952
-Baby Hyun-suk.
-That's even worse.

1390
00:56:29,018 --> 00:56:31,421
-Oh, no.
-Like baby DIVE, Baby Hyun-suk?

1391
00:56:31,488 --> 00:56:33,256
-Baby Hyun-suk?
-Baby Hyun-suk.

1392
00:56:33,323 --> 00:56:34,691
Baby Hyun-suk.

1393
00:56:34,758 --> 00:56:36,493
Of course, I accept this result.

1394
00:56:36,559 --> 00:56:38,661
Well, from now on,

1395
00:56:39,429 --> 00:56:40,964
I'll leave out comedy, saltiness,

1396
00:56:41,865 --> 00:56:43,099
and show.

1397
00:56:43,166 --> 00:56:45,268
-That makes you even more the same.
-And drop greasy too.

1398
00:56:45,335 --> 00:56:47,103
-And greasy.
-You two are the same.

1399
00:56:47,170 --> 00:56:49,773
I'll only focus on cooking
and try more seriously.

1400
00:56:49,839 --> 00:56:51,641
-I see.
-That was cool.

1401
00:56:51,708 --> 00:56:55,979
Chef Hyun-suk gets three stars
and becomes the first place!

1402
00:56:56,546 --> 00:56:58,848
Choi Hyun-suk is in first place!

1403
00:56:58,915 --> 00:57:00,083
Thank you.

1404
00:57:00,817 --> 00:57:03,386
Chef Sung-jun is washing his pan.

1405
00:57:03,453 --> 00:57:04,454
It's a little dirty.

1406
00:57:04,521 --> 00:57:06,122
He wants to wash it and give it to him.

1407
00:57:06,189 --> 00:57:07,824
It was his cherished pan.

1408
00:57:07,891 --> 00:57:10,460
It spent three months with me
through <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

1409
00:57:10,527 --> 00:57:12,262
-My gosh.
-That's huge.

1410
00:57:13,563 --> 00:57:14,798
Look at Poong.

1411
00:57:14,864 --> 00:57:18,468
-You're the true winner from this.
-He is.

1412
00:57:18,535 --> 00:57:23,473
CHOI HYUN-SUK'S LUCKY CHOI STEAK
THE RECIPE

1413
00:57:23,540 --> 00:57:25,141
I got a word from the production crew.

1414
00:57:25,208 --> 00:57:28,912
After the first round, Won-young took

1415
00:57:28,978 --> 00:57:31,514
-all the leftovers she had
-Yes?

1416
00:57:31,581 --> 00:57:35,552
-and took it to her green room.
-Whoa.

1417
00:57:35,618 --> 00:57:38,087
She's the first guest
to take the food to her green room.

1418
00:57:38,154 --> 00:57:40,156
-Really?
-My gosh.

1419
00:57:40,223 --> 00:57:42,892
It was so good, but I left it all behind

1420
00:57:42,959 --> 00:57:45,662
-because I had to talk.
-You couldn't eat it.

1421
00:57:45,728 --> 00:57:48,965
I took everything
and tasted both dishes once again.

1422
00:57:49,599 --> 00:57:50,600
PLEASED

1423
00:57:50,667 --> 00:57:53,703
-You wanted to eat some more, right?
-Yes.

1424
00:57:53,770 --> 00:57:54,904
She's so nice.

1425
00:57:54,971 --> 00:57:59,409
Next up, the second round
with Won-young's ingredients.

1426
00:57:59,476 --> 00:58:03,046
A star Italian chef who has one-star
here on <i>Chef & My Fridge </i>is

1427
00:58:03,112 --> 00:58:06,916
up against a star French chef.

1428
00:58:06,983 --> 00:58:09,352
The air is different
from the previous round.

1429
00:58:09,419 --> 00:58:12,622
Round one was rather rough and tough.

1430
00:58:12,689 --> 00:58:14,924
It was, but these two are very elegant.

1431
00:58:14,991 --> 00:58:19,262
I was a little surprised
thinking they might break out in a fight.

1432
00:58:19,829 --> 00:58:21,097
It was like <i>Show Me the Money</i>.

1433
00:58:21,164 --> 00:58:24,434
We can watch this round
with a bit more peace,

1434
00:58:24,501 --> 00:58:27,504
but the two are
still burning with the desire to win.

1435
00:58:27,570 --> 00:58:31,674
Chef Sam has had the worst luck
with his contenders.

1436
00:58:31,741 --> 00:58:36,045
Both his restaurants have won a star
in the Michelin guide. That isn't easy.

1437
00:58:36,112 --> 00:58:37,547
-Of course not.
-No.

1438
00:58:37,614 --> 00:58:38,815
But what if you win today?

1439
00:58:38,882 --> 00:58:41,718
First, you already took over
<i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

1440
00:58:41,784 --> 00:58:44,087
You'd also be taking
double stars from the Michelin guide.

1441
00:58:44,153 --> 00:58:46,122
-Right.
-Yes, you're right.

1442
00:58:46,189 --> 00:58:48,491
I'm actually more nervous now
than last week.

1443
00:58:48,558 --> 00:58:50,360
-Why?
-Why is that?

1444
00:58:50,426 --> 00:58:52,862
Because back then,
he was all showy and loud

1445
00:58:52,929 --> 00:58:54,697
just like Chef Hyun-suk.

1446
00:58:55,365 --> 00:58:57,534
THE TWO ARE SHOWY
AND LOUD IN THE SAME WAY

1447
00:58:57,600 --> 00:58:58,601
He meant that.

1448
00:58:58,668 --> 00:59:03,139
Yes, but true experts are rather quiet.

1449
00:59:03,206 --> 00:59:05,008
The two are underdogs?

1450
00:59:05,074 --> 00:59:06,476
-Underdogs?
-No, that's not it.

1451
00:59:06,543 --> 00:59:08,745
He feels quite different.

1452
00:59:09,312 --> 00:59:11,581
The production crew told me

1453
00:59:11,648 --> 00:59:14,450
that Chef Sam said something like this.

1454
00:59:15,552 --> 00:59:20,089
"I'll destroy Son Jong-won."

1455
00:59:21,090 --> 00:59:22,091
-What?
-Really?

1456
00:59:22,158 --> 00:59:25,562
It's not like he's a building.
How is he going to destroy him?

1457
00:59:25,628 --> 00:59:27,664
-Sam said that?
-That was unexpected.

1458
00:59:27,730 --> 00:59:29,198
How is he going to destroy him?

1459
00:59:29,265 --> 00:59:30,667
-Whoa.
-Let's check the facts.

1460
00:59:30,733 --> 00:59:32,001
Did you say that or not?

1461
00:59:32,068 --> 00:59:33,603
Well.

1462
00:59:33,670 --> 00:59:35,071
-He did.
-No way.

1463
00:59:35,138 --> 00:59:36,606
-I can tell by his face.
-No way.

1464
00:59:36,673 --> 00:59:38,474
-He said it.
-Yes, I did.

1465
00:59:39,075 --> 00:59:41,377
-Whoa.
-You really said it?

1466
00:59:41,444 --> 00:59:42,979
WE'VE NEVER SEEN
SAINT SAM LIKE THIS

1467
00:59:43,046 --> 00:59:45,515
-"Yes, I did."
-He admits it honestly.

1468
00:59:45,582 --> 00:59:48,618
The 15-minute rule we have
here on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> is

1469
00:59:48,685 --> 00:59:50,653
-harder than it seems.
-Of course.

1470
00:59:50,720 --> 00:59:55,725
I did say I wanted to show him
that <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> is a tough place.

1471
00:59:55,792 --> 00:59:56,960
-I see.
-I knew it.

1472
00:59:57,026 --> 01:00:01,898
Chef Jong-won looks a little rigid
after he heard those words.

1473
01:00:01,965 --> 01:00:03,499
How do you feel right now?

1474
01:00:03,566 --> 01:00:06,169
This was something
said by a chef who taught me.

1475
01:00:06,235 --> 01:00:09,372
It was,
"No one goes to the Olympics to lose."

1476
01:00:10,640 --> 01:00:11,641
-That's true.
-That's cool.

1477
01:00:11,708 --> 01:00:14,644
As you mentioned,
I do have a star in the Michelin guide,

1478
01:00:14,711 --> 01:00:17,280
but I don't have one on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

1479
01:00:17,347 --> 01:00:18,915
I'm here to take a star from Jang-chelin.

1480
01:00:20,917 --> 01:00:23,553
-I look forward to this.
-Jang-chelin.

1481
01:00:23,620 --> 01:00:24,821
Jang-chelin.

1482
01:00:24,887 --> 01:00:27,190
Eun-ji is losing her patience.

1483
01:00:27,256 --> 01:00:28,691
EUN-JI GETS MAD OUT OF JEALOUSY(?)

1484
01:00:29,993 --> 01:00:31,394
You're free to use a perk.

1485
01:00:31,461 --> 01:00:34,263
-Yes, right.
-The new chef can use a perk.

1486
01:00:34,330 --> 01:00:35,632
Will you use it?

1487
01:00:36,332 --> 01:00:39,502
-I actually prepared three dishes.
-Three.

1488
01:00:40,603 --> 01:00:43,006
-It's for fine dining.
-Three dishes in fifteen minutes?

1489
01:00:43,072 --> 01:00:45,742
So I'll begin a minute earlier.

1490
01:00:45,808 --> 01:00:47,977
-He gets 16 minutes.
-I see. A minute earlier.

1491
01:00:48,044 --> 01:00:50,647
Chef Sam, you just have to watch
for a minute.

1492
01:00:50,713 --> 01:00:52,682
This isn't so bad. It's doable.

1493
01:00:53,516 --> 01:00:55,618
CHEF SAM'S INGREDIENTS:
CAMEMBERT, ENDIVE,

1494
01:00:55,685 --> 01:00:57,587
MACADAMIA ICE CREAM,
ARUGULA, AND MORE

1495
01:00:57,654 --> 01:01:01,758
CHEF JONG-WON'S INGREDIENTS: ENDIVE,
RIB EYE, MACADAMIA ICE CREAM, AND MORE

1496
01:01:01,824 --> 01:01:05,094
I heard
you came straight from the airport.

1497
01:01:05,161 --> 01:01:06,195
You're right.

1498
01:01:06,262 --> 01:01:07,630
You live a busy life,

1499
01:01:07,697 --> 01:01:11,234
so I didn't think you had enough time
to sit and enjoy a meal.

1500
01:01:11,300 --> 01:01:13,536
I wanted you to do that
here on <i>Chef & My Fridge,</i>

1501
01:01:13,603 --> 01:01:16,973
so I'll make Jang-chelin Course Meal
in 15 minutes.

1502
01:01:17,040 --> 01:01:18,041
Thank you.

1503
01:01:18,107 --> 01:01:20,777
This introduction was already moving.

1504
01:01:21,444 --> 01:01:24,547
I already want to give him more points.

1505
01:01:25,248 --> 01:01:26,449
He's so sweet.

1506
01:01:26,516 --> 01:01:28,384
I want to use the pistachio spread

1507
01:01:28,451 --> 01:01:30,119
just as Chef Sung-jun did.

1508
01:01:30,186 --> 01:01:31,521
I prepared an endive salad.

1509
01:01:32,088 --> 01:01:33,222
I love it.

1510
01:01:33,289 --> 01:01:35,058
Was there some spread left?

1511
01:01:35,124 --> 01:01:37,994
It's almost gone, but it's okay.

1512
01:01:38,061 --> 01:01:39,896
Who used that much spread?

1513
01:01:39,962 --> 01:01:41,497
Did Chef Sung-jun use too much?

1514
01:01:41,564 --> 01:01:43,132
-He must've used a lot.
-It's okay.

1515
01:01:43,199 --> 01:01:45,601
Then I wanted to make rib eye steak

1516
01:01:45,668 --> 01:01:48,604
with wasabi, which you said you liked,

1517
01:01:48,671 --> 01:01:50,473
as well as Brussels sprouts.

1518
01:01:50,540 --> 01:01:52,575
Lastly, I'll use macadamia nuts
and make ice cream.

1519
01:01:52,642 --> 01:01:54,243
That sounds so delicious.

1520
01:01:54,310 --> 01:01:56,079
Macadamia.

1521
01:01:56,145 --> 01:01:57,980
What I prepared today is called

1522
01:01:58,047 --> 01:02:00,116
Won-young's Course Meal.

1523
01:02:00,183 --> 01:02:02,552
-I see.
-Won-young's Course Meal.

1524
01:02:02,618 --> 01:02:06,756
The color red is
something that symbolizes Won-young,

1525
01:02:06,823 --> 01:02:09,025
so I'll use red as a theme

1526
01:02:09,092 --> 01:02:11,027
to make pretty dishes.

1527
01:02:11,094 --> 01:02:12,795
Gosh, thank you so much.

1528
01:02:12,862 --> 01:02:15,865
I prepared some beet as an appetizer.

1529
01:02:15,932 --> 01:02:17,900
-I love beets.
-The red from beets.

1530
01:02:17,967 --> 01:02:21,637
You said you liked chuck flap tail,
so I'll grill that lightly.

1531
01:02:21,704 --> 01:02:24,140
I also prepared dessert with strawberries.

1532
01:02:24,207 --> 01:02:27,276
-Everything is themed around red.
-Yes.

1533
01:02:27,343 --> 01:02:29,479
And now, we'll begin

1534
01:02:29,545 --> 01:02:33,382
"Hold your breath, love dining" round
with Won-young's ingredients.

1535
01:02:33,449 --> 01:02:35,685
It wasn't enough
that he already had double stars

1536
01:02:35,752 --> 01:02:38,454
in the Michelin guide,
so he's here to take our stars.

1537
01:02:38,521 --> 01:02:42,625
The good vibes guy of classy restaurants,
Chef Son Jong-won.

1538
01:02:43,593 --> 01:02:45,795
He's up against this man
who'll destroy the double Michelin stars

1539
01:02:45,862 --> 01:02:47,997
and win double <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> stars,

1540
01:02:48,064 --> 01:02:50,133
the Grim Reaper to new chefs,

1541
01:02:50,199 --> 01:02:52,769
Chef Sam Kim.

1542
01:02:52,835 --> 01:02:56,539
Chef Jong-won will begin first!

1543
01:02:56,606 --> 01:02:59,008
SON JONG-WON USES HIS 1-MINUTE EARLY PERK

1544
01:02:59,075 --> 01:03:00,109
Begin first!

1545
01:03:01,978 --> 01:03:03,446
-You can do this!
-He begins a minute earlier.

1546
01:03:03,513 --> 01:03:05,081
You can do this!

1547
01:03:05,148 --> 01:03:06,916
Chef Jong-won gets a minute first.

1548
01:03:06,983 --> 01:03:09,786
-Whoa, look.
-He looks composed.

1549
01:03:10,353 --> 01:03:11,687
-He's smiling.
-Yes.

1550
01:03:11,754 --> 01:03:13,222
He remains calm.

1551
01:03:13,289 --> 01:03:14,290
Plastic wrap?

1552
01:03:14,357 --> 01:03:15,725
He has to make three dishes.

1553
01:03:16,526 --> 01:03:17,927
He's using plastic wrap.

1554
01:03:17,994 --> 01:03:20,229
And he's wiping it with cloth.

1555
01:03:20,296 --> 01:03:21,898
And he removes the wrap.

1556
01:03:21,964 --> 01:03:23,366
CHUCKLES

1557
01:03:23,432 --> 01:03:24,634
When only one person cooks,

1558
01:03:24,700 --> 01:03:26,536
-he gets all our attention.
-He does.

1559
01:03:26,602 --> 01:03:28,404
Truffle oil. Do you have truffle oil?

1560
01:03:28,471 --> 01:03:29,705
I don't.

1561
01:03:29,772 --> 01:03:31,340
What's he doing?

1562
01:03:31,407 --> 01:03:33,242
-He's losing time.
-He needs truffle oil.

1563
01:03:33,309 --> 01:03:34,644
-Truffle oil.
-It was there.

1564
01:03:34,710 --> 01:03:37,113
-It was right in front of you.
-He changed it.

1565
01:03:37,180 --> 01:03:39,282
-Truffle oil is here.
-It's there.

1566
01:03:39,348 --> 01:03:41,117
-Should I take it?
-It's okay.

1567
01:03:41,184 --> 01:03:42,852
There's truffle oil.

1568
01:03:42,919 --> 01:03:45,054
You didn't take truffle oil?

1569
01:03:46,022 --> 01:03:48,524
-You already lost the minute.
-Look, it's 14, 13 seconds.

1570
01:03:48,591 --> 01:03:50,126
He just lost time.

1571
01:03:51,194 --> 01:03:52,395
The minute is up.

1572
01:03:52,461 --> 01:03:53,996
-Here, Chef Jong-won.
-The time is ticking.

1573
01:03:54,063 --> 01:03:57,900
All he did for a minute was
set out the plastic wrap.

1574
01:03:57,967 --> 01:03:59,635
Chef Sam, please get ready.

1575
01:03:59,702 --> 01:04:01,237
-Four. Three.
-What's he doing?

1576
01:04:01,304 --> 01:04:03,272
-Two. One.
-No, you can do this.

1577
01:04:03,339 --> 01:04:05,274
-Begin!
-Chef Sam may begin.

1578
01:04:05,341 --> 01:04:07,610
-Begin!
-Chef Sam may begin.

1579
01:04:07,677 --> 01:04:08,911
-Gosh.
-You can do it!

1580
01:04:08,978 --> 01:04:10,713
He hasn't done much for a minute.

1581
01:04:10,780 --> 01:04:13,349
He really spent the minute doing that.

1582
01:04:13,416 --> 01:04:15,551
How will he make three dishes?

1583
01:04:15,618 --> 01:04:17,653
No, you've done well.

1584
01:04:17,720 --> 01:04:18,721
CLICK

1585
01:04:20,156 --> 01:04:21,824
Is that macadamia ice cream?

1586
01:04:21,891 --> 01:04:23,793
-He's starting with dessert.
-It's the dessert.

1587
01:04:23,860 --> 01:04:25,728
He seems to be making dessert first.

1588
01:04:25,795 --> 01:04:27,830
-That was dessert?
-Are you mixing egg yolk and sugar?

1589
01:04:27,897 --> 01:04:29,899
2. PUT MACADAMIA ICE CREAM
ON CHESTNUT JAM

1590
01:04:29,966 --> 01:04:31,801
AND MAKE IT INTO A BALL,
THEN FREEZE

1591
01:04:31,868 --> 01:04:33,302
He's putting it in the freezer.

1592
01:04:33,369 --> 01:04:35,204
That looks really good.

1593
01:04:35,271 --> 01:04:38,541
He put the dessert in the freezer.

1594
01:04:38,608 --> 01:04:41,177
-Chef Sam is breaking eggs.
-Yes.

1595
01:04:41,244 --> 01:04:43,079
Yes, I need just egg yolks.

1596
01:04:43,145 --> 01:04:44,447
He's getting egg yolks.

1597
01:04:44,513 --> 01:04:46,182
You're mixing egg yolk and sugar?

1598
01:04:46,249 --> 01:04:47,250
Yes, sugar.

1599
01:04:47,316 --> 01:04:49,986
-Chef Sam got ice cream first, too.
-Yes.

1600
01:04:50,052 --> 01:04:52,521
-Did he mix egg and ice cream?
-He did.

1601
01:04:52,588 --> 01:04:55,458
-The both chose macadamia ice cream.
-Yes.

1602
01:04:56,259 --> 01:04:57,260
Is that so?

1603
01:04:57,326 --> 01:04:59,795
-The both chose macadamia ice cream.
-Yes.

1604
01:04:59,862 --> 01:05:01,364
It's still plugged.

1605
01:05:01,430 --> 01:05:03,666
-How do I open this?
-Why is it plugged?

1606
01:05:03,733 --> 01:05:05,167
-I want to open it for him.
-This isn't good.

1607
01:05:05,234 --> 01:05:07,069
-I got it.
-Someone do it for him.

1608
01:05:07,136 --> 01:05:08,671
You should've checked that first.

1609
01:05:08,738 --> 01:05:10,006
I got it. It's okay.

1610
01:05:10,072 --> 01:05:11,741
Is that black pepper? What's that?

1611
01:05:11,807 --> 01:05:13,309
What is that?

1612
01:05:13,743 --> 01:05:15,811
I don't know. It was yours.

1613
01:05:15,878 --> 01:05:17,346
What was… I didn't see it.

1614
01:05:17,413 --> 01:05:18,681
Vanilla beans.

1615
01:05:18,748 --> 01:05:20,016
-Vanilla beans.
-Vanilla beans.

1616
01:05:20,082 --> 01:05:21,550
-I do have vanilla beans.
-You had that?

1617
01:05:21,617 --> 01:05:23,019
-It was that.
-You had vanilla beans?

1618
01:05:23,085 --> 01:05:25,421
I had them in a grinder.

1619
01:05:25,488 --> 01:05:26,722
You have vanilla beans too?

1620
01:05:26,789 --> 01:05:28,624
There's a vanilla bean grinder?

1621
01:05:29,659 --> 01:05:33,562
2. MIX EGG YOLKS, SUGAR, ICE CREAM,
AND VANILLA BEAN

1622
01:05:33,629 --> 01:05:35,398
TO MAKE ZABAIONE SAUCE

1623
01:05:35,965 --> 01:05:38,000
OLIVE OIL

1624
01:05:39,068 --> 01:05:43,105
3. SEASON RIB EYE
WITH GROUND PEPPER AND SALT

1625
01:05:46,542 --> 01:05:47,910
The meat is in.

1626
01:05:47,977 --> 01:05:50,112
Chef Jong-won just dropped rib eye.

1627
01:05:50,179 --> 01:05:51,180
Is that rib eye?

1628
01:05:51,247 --> 01:05:52,982
HE CAN'T HEAR YOU

1629
01:05:53,049 --> 01:05:56,285
My gosh. Your veins look cool on the arms.

1630
01:05:56,352 --> 01:05:57,553
I see.

1631
01:05:57,620 --> 01:05:59,722
He must've heard you.

1632
01:05:59,789 --> 01:06:02,124
Chef Jong-won is showing a big smile.

1633
01:06:02,758 --> 01:06:03,893
FLUTTER!

1634
01:06:03,960 --> 01:06:06,462
HE GRABS THE PAN WITH A TOWEL

1635
01:06:10,833 --> 01:06:11,901
And Brussels sprouts.

1636
01:06:11,968 --> 01:06:13,836
Be careful with those.

1637
01:06:15,338 --> 01:06:16,505
They're delicious.

1638
01:06:17,306 --> 01:06:18,975
WHAT ABOUT SAM KIM'S VEGGIES?

1639
01:06:19,041 --> 01:06:20,576
RED-THEMED: BEET

1640
01:06:20,643 --> 01:06:23,245
-The beet looks fresh.
-It's so red.

1641
01:06:23,312 --> 01:06:25,247
I really love beets.

1642
01:06:25,314 --> 01:06:27,550
-You said that was the appetizer.
-You're right.

1643
01:06:27,616 --> 01:06:30,219
One of them uses beet,
the other uses Brussels sprouts.

1644
01:06:30,286 --> 01:06:32,455
-They're cooking with everything you like.
-Yes.

1645
01:06:32,521 --> 01:06:34,423
I love Brussels sprouts too.

1646
01:06:34,991 --> 01:06:36,092
Brussels sprout.

1647
01:06:36,158 --> 01:06:37,493
POURING

1648
01:06:37,560 --> 01:06:38,928
The sauce and…

1649
01:06:38,995 --> 01:06:40,796
-Right.
-Isn't that balsamic vinegar?

1650
01:06:40,863 --> 01:06:42,098
He's boiling down white balsamic vinegar.

1651
01:06:42,698 --> 01:06:43,866
Balsamic vinegar?

1652
01:06:43,933 --> 01:06:45,534
-I see.
-And sugar.

1653
01:06:45,601 --> 01:06:47,169
He mixes balsamic vinegar and sugar.

1654
01:06:47,236 --> 01:06:50,506
White balsamic vinegar is
much less sour than the regular one,

1655
01:06:50,573 --> 01:06:52,641
and it's much sweeter.

1656
01:06:52,708 --> 01:06:55,945
So if he boiled that with sugar,
it'd be like what she mentioned.

1657
01:06:56,012 --> 01:06:57,713
-You said it was like fruit.
-It was like fruit.

1658
01:06:59,081 --> 01:07:03,219
6. ADD SLICED BEET TO THE WHITE
BALSAMIC SYRUP AND BOIL DOWN

1659
01:07:03,285 --> 01:07:04,587
He's using it as sauce.

1660
01:07:06,522 --> 01:07:08,657
He's boiling Brussels sprouts.

1661
01:07:08,724 --> 01:07:10,159
-He's frying them.
-He is?

1662
01:07:10,226 --> 01:07:11,927
-He is?
-He's frying them in oil.

1663
01:07:11,994 --> 01:07:14,897
-That sounds so good.
-He's deep-frying them.

1664
01:07:14,964 --> 01:07:15,998
It'll pop. Be careful.

1665
01:07:16,065 --> 01:07:17,466
Will it? How?

1666
01:07:17,533 --> 01:07:18,601
-What will pop?
-What?

1667
01:07:18,667 --> 01:07:20,469
Brussels sprouts have

1668
01:07:20,536 --> 01:07:23,105
-layers of leaves.
-Yes, the air bubbles.

1669
01:07:23,172 --> 01:07:25,007
Please be careful.

1670
01:07:25,074 --> 01:07:26,575
But he cut them, so it'll be fine.

1671
01:07:26,642 --> 01:07:29,645
It'd become a mess
if he fried it without cutting them.

1672
01:07:29,712 --> 01:07:31,914
-He cut everything in half.
-Yes.

1673
01:07:31,981 --> 01:07:33,416
Be careful.

1674
01:07:35,084 --> 01:07:37,520
-What was that?
-He stuck a needle in

1675
01:07:37,586 --> 01:07:38,587
and put it on his chin.

1676
01:07:38,654 --> 01:07:39,955
He stuck a needle in
and put it on his chin?

1677
01:07:40,022 --> 01:07:43,459
It's not easy to tell
if the steak has been cooked well.

1678
01:07:43,526 --> 01:07:46,328
So we put the needle
inside the wrist or here.

1679
01:07:46,395 --> 01:07:48,531
If it's hot, it'll be well done.
If it's warm, it'll be medium.

1680
01:07:48,597 --> 01:07:52,034
If it's lukewarm, it's medium-rare.
We can tell by the temperature.

1681
01:07:53,502 --> 01:07:56,238
He's pouring greasy on the rib eye.

1682
01:07:56,305 --> 01:07:58,541
When Chef Jong-won began to cook,

1683
01:07:58,607 --> 01:08:01,544
-he stopped smiling altogether.
-Yes, he did.

1684
01:08:01,610 --> 01:08:03,779
-He seems composed yet fast.
-Yes.

1685
01:08:05,181 --> 01:08:07,583
Is the steak done already?

1686
01:08:07,650 --> 01:08:10,386
Chef Jong-won is resting the steak.

1687
01:08:10,453 --> 01:08:12,455
-Resting.
-Yes.

1688
01:08:12,521 --> 01:08:14,256
What about the garlic clove?

1689
01:08:14,323 --> 01:08:16,258
-To add some flavor.
-Flavor.

1690
01:08:16,325 --> 01:08:17,793
He's using cheese.

1691
01:08:17,860 --> 01:08:19,195
SAM KIM'S SECOND SAUCE,
CAMEMBERT CHEESE

1692
01:08:20,029 --> 01:08:24,500
7. ADD CAMEMBERT TO MILK
AND DOUBLE BOIL TO MAKE CHEESE SAUCE

1693
01:08:24,567 --> 01:08:26,936
They're both making three dishes.

1694
01:08:27,002 --> 01:08:31,040
They're making three dishes,
so we don't know what's what.

1695
01:08:31,107 --> 01:08:32,508
