1832
01:14:05,874 --> 01:14:07,776
It's like custard cream.

1833
01:14:07,843 --> 01:14:09,344
What about the meat?

1834
01:14:09,411 --> 01:14:12,114
-I'll grill the meat.
-The meat.

1835
01:14:12,181 --> 01:14:14,716
Everything here looks beautiful.

1836
01:14:15,284 --> 01:14:18,120
-Do you have an opener?
-He went to borrow something.

1837
01:14:18,187 --> 01:14:19,855
-He borrowed something.
-What is it?

1838
01:14:19,922 --> 01:14:20,923
An opener.

1839
01:14:20,989 --> 01:14:22,925
-A macadamia opener.
-I see.

1840
01:14:22,991 --> 01:14:25,594
-You have too many things to do.
-You're supposed to open it.

1841
01:14:25,661 --> 01:14:27,162
You had to open it.

1842
01:14:27,229 --> 01:14:29,064
It'll take you a long time.

1843
01:14:29,131 --> 01:14:30,332
-I see.
-A macadamia nut.

1844
01:14:30,399 --> 01:14:32,367
