-Yes?

1854
01:14:52,221 --> 01:14:54,623
Can you check
if the Brussels sprouts are burnt?

1855
01:14:54,690 --> 01:14:58,494
-These look burnt. They're quite dark.
-Yes.

1856
01:14:58,560 --> 01:15:00,295
It looks good.

1857
01:15:00,362 --> 01:15:01,763
Should I try this?

1858
01:15:02,798 --> 01:15:04,299
He checks the Brussels sprouts.

1859
01:15:05,033 --> 01:15:06,101
Is it burnt?

1860
01:15:06,168 --> 01:15:08,370
-Whoa.
-What? Why?

1861
01:15:09,104 --> 01:15:10,639
It's burnt, but why is it delicious?

1862
01:15:10,706 --> 01:15:13,509
I see. It's good?

1863
01:15:13,575 --> 01:15:15,244
-It's good?
-It tastes burnt.

1864
01:15:15,310 --> 01:15:17,179
It's a little bitter too.

1865
01:15:17,246 --> 01:15:19,248
But it also tastes sweet.

1866
01:15:19,314 --> 01:15:20,649
-Gosh.
-What?

1867
01:15:20,716 --> 01:15:23,252
I don't think he cares
about Won-young's health.

1868
01:15:25,654 --> 01:15:27,489
