-What is it?

1924
01:17:41,890 --> 01:17:45,193
-What are you asking for?
-What is it? Hurry.

1925
01:17:45,260 --> 01:17:46,528
-Find it.
-What is it?

1926
01:17:47,229 --> 01:17:49,264
A minute and 30 seconds!

1927
01:17:49,331 --> 01:17:51,733
1 MINUTE AND 30 SECONDS LEFT

1928
01:17:51,800 --> 01:17:53,435
Darn it.

1929
01:17:53,502 --> 01:17:54,670
What's wrong?

1930
01:17:54,736 --> 01:17:56,838
We got a "darn it" from Chef Jong-won!

1931
01:17:57,639 --> 01:17:58,874
We got a "darn it"!

1932
01:17:58,940 --> 01:17:59,941
He does say swear words.

1933
01:18:00,008 --> 01:18:01,176
Oh, no.

1934
01:18:01,243 --> 01:18:03,478
I should've bought peeled macadamia nuts.

1935
01:18:03,545 --> 01:18:04,880
Right?

1936
01:18:04,946 --> 01:18:07,582
-It's not over yet.
-The ice cream. Is this dessert?

1937
01:18:07,649 --> 01:18:08,917
-The ice cream.
-The ice cream.

1938
01:18:08,984 --> 01:18:10,619
16. PUT ICE CREAM
IN CHILLED MARTINI GLASS

1939
01:18:10,686 --> 01:18:12,287
SERVE WITH VANILLA MACADAMIA,
TRUFFLE OIL

1940
01:18:12,354 --> 01:18:13,955
-He wrapped ice cream with cheese.
-Yes.

1941
01:18:14,022 --> 01:18:17,192
It was ice cream wrapped with goat cheese.

1942
01:18:17,259 --> 01:18:20,495
-That looks good. Truffle oil!
-He makes it look easy.

1943
01:18:20,562 --> 01:18:22,197
They have similar styles.

1944
01:18:22,264 --> 01:18:25,500
-They really do.
-Right? They do seem similar.

1945
01:18:25,567 --> 01:18:27,836
-Are you done?
-I'm done.

1946
01:18:27,903 --> 01:18:29,571
Chef Sam is done!

1947
01:18:30,172 --> 01:18:31,640
-Chef Sam finishes first.
-Less than a minute.

1948
01:18:31,707 --> 01:18:33,909
You have 45 seconds.

1949
01:18:33,975 --> 01:18:34,976
He even pours oil.

1950
01:18:35,043 --> 01:18:37,679
He's putting in a lot of effort
into plating the dishes.

1951
01:18:37,746 --> 01:18:40,315
-He started a minute early.
-What is it?

1952
01:18:40,382 --> 01:18:41,650
Hurry up.

1953
01:18:41,717 --> 01:18:43,051
-He has 30 seconds.
-It's 35 seconds!

1954
01:18:43,118 --> 01:18:44,352
You can do this!

1955
01:18:45,153 --> 01:18:47,022
-He's using tweezers.
-Tweezers!

1956
01:18:47,089 --> 01:18:48,623
Tweezers!

1957
01:18:48,690 --> 01:18:50,358
Do you have hand tremor?

1958
01:18:50,425 --> 01:18:52,094
He trembles his hands.

1959
01:18:52,160 --> 01:18:54,062
You have 25 seconds.

1960
01:18:54,129 --> 01:18:55,497
He's trembling his hands.

1961
01:18:56,698 --> 01:18:59,000
THE LAST LEAF
OF THE JANG-CHELIN COURSE MEAL

1962
01:18:59,067 --> 01:19:00,802
And now, ten seconds.

1963
01:19:01,369 --> 01:19:03,505
HOW WILL THE MICHELIN GUIDE
DOUBLE-STAR DO

1964
01:19:03,572 --> 01:19:04,873
AFTER HIS FIRST CHALLENGE?

1965
01:19:05,540 --> 01:19:07,909
How did they do this in 15 minutes?

1966
01:19:07,976 --> 01:19:09,077
It's really pretty.

1967
01:19:09,644 --> 01:19:10,645
My gosh.

1968
01:19:14,149 --> 01:19:15,283
WON-YOUNG BECOMES HAPPY VICKY

1969
01:19:15,350 --> 01:19:17,986
-Who did Won-young choose?
-Who is it?

1970
01:19:18,053 --> 01:19:19,254
Let's not open it.

1971
01:19:19,321 --> 01:19:21,156
We present Eun-ji's fridge!

1972
01:19:21,990 --> 01:19:23,692
Something just dropped.

1973
01:19:23,759 --> 01:19:25,660
I see a lot of soup.

1974
01:19:25,727 --> 01:19:27,028
No, don't open it.

1975
01:19:27,095 --> 01:19:28,764
-Don't do that!
-Throw it out.

1976
01:19:28,830 --> 01:19:31,466
Will you just do it there
instead of bringing it over?

1977
01:19:31,533 --> 01:19:35,537
The fastest chef in <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>,
Chef Yeon-bok.

1978
01:19:35,604 --> 01:19:40,075
He's up against Chef Kang-rok,
the slowest chef on the show.

1979
01:19:40,142 --> 01:19:41,576
What are you doing right now?

1980
01:19:41,643 --> 01:19:42,978
What are you doing right now?

1981
01:19:43,044 --> 01:19:44,679
I'm Jang Won-young, here on the scene.

1982
01:19:45,247 --> 01:19:46,248
And?

1983
01:19:46,314 --> 01:19:47,582
It's sour!

1984
01:19:47,649 --> 01:19:48,984
It tastes like fried <i>ramyeon</i>.

1985
01:19:49,050 --> 01:19:51,286
It tastes like fried <i>ramyeon</i>.

1986
01:19:51,353 --> 01:19:52,788
It's me, Announcer Jang.

1987
01:19:52,854 --> 01:19:56,725
-What is that?
-What's that? It looks like frog legs.

1988
01:19:56,792 --> 01:19:58,193
Hey, you lunatic!

1989
01:19:58,260 --> 01:20:00,061
WHAT'S THE DISH
THAT KILLED EVERYONE?

1990
01:20:00,128 --> 01:20:02,164
What is that?

1991
01:20:05,333 --> 01:20:07,335
Yes, I'm here at the scene.

1992
01:20:07,402 --> 01:20:09,871
Let him rest. Let Kang-rok take a break.

1993
01:20:17,879 --> 01:20:22,884
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
